.TH "dp_aux_transfer_helper" 9 "dp_aux_transfer_helper" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
dp_aux_transfer_helper \- helper function for EDID read transactions
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" dp_aux_transfer_helper
.BI "(struct dp_aux_private *aux "  ","
.BI "struct drm_dp_aux_msg *input_msg "  ","
.BI "bool send_seg "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "aux" 12
DP AUX private structure
.IP "input_msg" 12
input message from DRM upstream APIs
.IP "send_seg" 12
send the segment to sink
.SH "RETURN"
void
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This helper function is used to fix EDID reads for non-compliant
sinks that do not handle the i2c middle-of-transaction flag correctly.
